\subsection{Poincar&eacute; series}
\begin{definition}\label{specialfunction.poincare}
\uses{cmf.cusp_form,group.fuchsian.cusps,group.fuchsian.cusps.width,group.sl2z,group.subgroup.index,mf.multipliersystem,mf.upper_half_plane}
Let $G$ be a subgroup of {{KNOWL('group.sl2z', "$\Gamma$")}} of finite {{KNOWL('group.subgroup.index', "index")}} $m$, $v$ a {{KNOWL('mf.multipliersystem', "multiplier system")}} on $G$ and $k\geq3\in\mathbb{N}$ such that $v(-I)=(-1)^k$. Let $s$ be a {{KNOWL('group.fuchsian.cusps', "cusp")}} representative of $G$ with {{KNOWL('group.fuchsian.cusps.width', "width")}} $w$ such that $s=\gamma_s(\infty)$ for some $\gamma_s\in\Gamma$ and let $G_s=G\cap\gamma_s\Gamma_\infty\gamma_s^{-1}$ be the *stabilizer* of the cusp $s$. Assume that $v$ is trivial on $G_s$. The **$n$th Poincar&eacute; series** for the cusp that $s$ represents is defined as
\[
P_k^n(G,v;z;\overline{s})=\sum_{g\in G_s\setminus G}\overline{v(g)}e^{2\pi 
i(n/w)\gamma_s^{-1}gz}j(\gamma_s^{-1}g,z)^{-k},
\]
where $j(\gamma,z)=cz+d$ for $\gamma=\left(\begin{matrix}a&b\\c&d\end{matrix}\right)$. 

Poincar&eacute; series are *holomorphic* on the {{KNOWL('mf.upper_half_plane', "upper half-plane")}}. Further more, for a fixed cusp $\overline{S}$, they generate the corresponding space of {{KNOWL('cmf.cusp_form', "cusp forms")}}. The series depends on the choice of $\gamma_s$ up to a factor of $e^{2\pi in/w}$, therefore, if $w\mid n$, it does not depend on the cusp representative. 
\end{definition}


